Description.Text: ***Please note the address is 8-18 Inverness Terrace, London W2 3HU, and the reception is open between 8 am to 00:00h, so if you are arriving after that time, you might need to call the phone number displayed in the door plate or 0044 (0) 7985379609***

This property is located next to Hyde Park in the heart of London, set in a quiet side street, and just a minute walk from Queensway and Bayswater underground stations. The perfect location to visit every museum, shopping street and attraction London has to offer to leisure and business travelers alike.

The studios are all of a very good size, much larger than average London hotel rooms. They are all very modern and in excellent condition (having all been refurbished in 2007). They are airy and minimalist, painted in soft cream colours with very modern black and white furniture. All rooms have a brand new and very convenient kitchenette in one corner of the room. The bathrooms are small but of same high standards as the bedrooms. All bedrooms have wooden floors and some additional sitting space.

The property is made up of several, white facade Georgian town houses. They have all been linked and totally refurbished maintaining the original features of the period when they were built, creating a sharp contrast with the crisp modern interiors.
This property does not provide meals, so there is no restaurant, but there are plenty of restaurants and cafes in the area, a well known place for it's Chinese and middle eastern restaurants.

The small to medium lobby is decorated following the very modern and minimalist style of the bedrooms. Very modern, it has a small check-in desk and adjacent seating area, dominated by a huge, leaded, original window. ***Please note the address is 8-18 Inverness Terrace, London W2 3HU, and the reception is open between 8 am to 00:00h, so if you are arriving after that time, you might need to call the phone number displayed in the door plate or 0044 (0) 7985379609***
